            <fr:anchor>25134</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/5993</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>unstable-5993.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Baby steps in higher domain theory › the partial map classifier of a synthetic {\mathopen{}\left(\infty,1\right)\mathclose{}}-category"><fr:link href="jms-00RN.xml" title="Baby steps in higher domain theory" addr="jms-00RN" type="local">Baby steps in higher domain theory</fr:link> › the partial map classifier of a synthetic <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\infty ,1\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-category</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Assuming the higher Phoa principle, <fr:link href="leonipugh.xml" title="Leoni Pugh" addr="leonipugh" type="local">Leoni</fr:link> has deduced that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a Segal type, then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>It is not difficult, using results of <fr:link href="ulrikbuchholtz.xml" title="Ulrik Buchholtz" addr="ulrikbuchholtz" type="local">Buchholtz</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jonathanweinberger.xml" title="Jonathan Weinberger" addr="jonathanweinberger" type="local">Weinberger</fr:link>, to show that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is Rezk, then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Thus, synthetic <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\infty ,1\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-categories are closed under partial map classifiers: a necessary first step to a theory of higher domains.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
